  <section class="hw-faq-section" id="faqs">
    <div class="hw-container">
      <div class="hw-section-header">
        <h2 class="hw-section-title">Huawei Repair FAQs</h2>
        <p class="hw-section-subtitle">Common questions about Huawei repair at Mobile Tech Lab in Winnipeg</p>
      </div>
      <div class="hw-faq-list">
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Huawei phones in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — we're one of the few repair shops in Winnipeg that specializes in Huawei devices including P series, Mate, Nova, and all Honor models. Most shops turn Huawei repairs away due to parts sourcing challenges — we've built dedicated supplier relationships specifically to service these devices.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Are Huawei parts available in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">We maintain specialist supplier relationships for Huawei and Honor parts that most Canadian shops cannot source. Most common parts are available within 2–3 business days — contact us with your specific model to confirm availability before visiting.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>How long does Huawei screen repair take in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Most Huawei screen replacements are completed same-day in 1–2 hours once parts are in stock at our Winnipeg location. If your model requires a special order, we'll give you an estimated wait time when you contact us for a quote.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Honor phones in Winnipeg?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all Honor devices including the Magic series, Honor 50, Honor 70, and all legacy Honor models. Honor shares many components with Huawei and our supplier relationships cover both brands.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you repair Huawei phones without Google services?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair all Huawei hardware regardless of whether the device runs Google Mobile Services or Huawei Mobile Services. Our repairs are hardware-only and do not affect the software or app ecosystem on your device.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix Huawei SuperCharge not working?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — SuperCharge failures are a common Huawei issue we diagnose and repair regularly. We test the full charging chain including the USB-C port, charging IC, and battery to identify the specific fault before recommending any repair.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Huawei Leica camera issues?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair front and rear camera modules on all Huawei P series and Mate series devices including the Leica-engineered multi-lens systems. Camera repairs include blurry images, black screen, autofocus failures, and cracked lens glass.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Can you fix a Huawei phone that won't turn on?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — a non-responsive Huawei is often caused by a depleted battery, a software boot loop, or a component-level board fault. We run free diagnostics to identify the root cause before recommending any repair so you know what the issue is before spending anything.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Huawei in-display fingerprint sensors?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — we repair and recalibrate in-display optical fingerprint sensors on Huawei P and Mate series flagships, as well as rear fingerprint sensors on Nova and entry-level models. Fingerprint sensor issues are often caused by screen replacement with incompatible parts — we use model-matched components to avoid this.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="hw-faq-item">
          <summary class="hw-faq-summary">
            <span>Do you repair Huawei phones in Thompson, MB?</span>
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="hw-faq-chevron" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false"><path d="m6 9 6 6 6-6"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <p class="hw-faq-answer">Yes — our Thompson location at 300 Mystery Lake Rd #1530 accepts Huawei repairs Monday through Saturday 10AM–6PM. For less common Huawei models, calling ahead helps us confirm parts availability before your visit.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

